    • Francccssion

      public Francccssion​(int num, int denom)
      Creates a fraction num/denom. Expresses negative values interms of -num/denom. If denom is negative and the num is positive,it is converted to a negative num and a positive denom. If denom is negative and num is negative too, then is converts to a positive num and denom. When the num is zero, denom is set to 1. Zero is always represented as 0/1
      Parameters:
      num - the numerator
      denom - the denominator
